    "title": "Modify rotation and positioning programmatically"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can implement your own inference and tracking to directly control the velocity or position of the docking station. To do this, use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.DockKit/documentation/DockKit/DockAccessoryManager/setSystemTrackingEnabled(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to prevent system from automatically tracking subjects.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "do {",
            "    try await DockAccessoryManager.shared.setSystemTrackingEnabled(false)",
            "} catch {",
            "   // Handle any errors.",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After disabling tracking, use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.DockKit/documentation/DockKit/DockAccessoryManager/accessoryStateChanges",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to iterate through the available accessories and find the one you wish to interact with.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Once you identify the accessory of interest use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.DockKit/documentation/DockKit/DockAccessory/setAngularVelocity(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.DockKit/documentation/DockKit/DockAccessory/setOrientation(_:duration:relative:)-2epe2",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.DockKit/documentation/DockKit/DockAccessory/setOrientation(_:duration:relative:)-6b0fl",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to directly control the speed and position of the accessory:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "do {",
            "    // Set angular velocity in radians per second.",
            "    // On iOS, pitch is downwards.",
            "    let vector = Vector3D(x: pitch, y: yaw, z: roll)",
            "    try await dockAccessory.setAngularVelocity(vector)",
            "",
            "    // Set rotational position and wait for updates as the accessory executes a trajectory.",
            "    let rotation = Rotation3D(eulerAngles: EulerAngles(x: Angle2D(radians: yaw), y: Angle2D(radians: pitch), z: Angle2D(radians: roll), order: __SPEulerAngleOrder.xyz))",
            "    // NOTE: You can also initialize from quaternions:",
            "    // let pos = Rotation3D(quaternion: simd_quatd)",
            "    // Monitor or KVO-observe progress toward the orientation goal.",
            "    let progress = try dockAccessory.setOrientation(rotation, duration: .seconds(duration), relative: relative)",
            "       // Do something with orientation progress.",
            "    }",
            "} catch {",
            "    // Handle any errors.",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The system tracking enabled state isnâ€™t guaranteed to persist across reboots, app launch/termination, or background/foreground states. Enable or disable system tracking whenever your app needs the value to change.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Changes to the tracking are local to the app, and are changeable dynamically anytime during app lifecycle.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
